Constructed from Mil-Spec hard-anodized aluminum, they feed smoothly and reliably due to optimal geometry, non-binding coil springs, and ingenious nesting polymer followers. The 100-round magazine—slightly thinner than two 30-round magazines clipped together and about the same overall length—fits in most dual magazine pouches, eliminating special carry pouches required for drum magazines. title: Want To Buy:  Gunsmith Shop Manager – Salary $35,000 a year, plus bonus’ and benefits.
postcontent:
I am in the planning phase of building a new gun club in the south metro area. 
This is an opportunity to get in on the ground floor, help us design the perfect shop and select the correct tools and people for the job.  

The club will be touting a Gunsmith Shop capable of modern firearm Safety Checks or Civil War Era Restorations. This manager will be in charge of the Shop and the Firing Range. Due to possible lead exposure on the range, all Gunsmiths will be certified as RSO’s, and eventually sales staff can be certified as well. This will allow us to perform a staff rotation of one on, three off the range. Starting, the Shop Manager will lead 3 other Gunsmiths. As sales staff is certified, the Shop Manager will be able to include these personnel in the RSO schedule rotation.  
You will be responsible for bound book entries for firearm maintenance (I am exploring ebound book software), Shop staff scheduling, Shop staff training, advising executive management on prices for services (public pricing, and club member pricing), tool and supply purchases, proper disposal of spent shop supplies, creating estimates for service, budgeting, customer service, and other duties as assigned. The Shop counter will be equipped with a Point Of Sale system to charge for services, but the cash handling will be managed by the Pro Shop Manager. 

•	Experience as a Gunsmith is required. 
•	Pass a background check to be added to the FFL, required.
•	Experience as a shop manger preferred.
•	NRA Certifications preferred. (Pay increases with certifications)
•	Basic computer operation required. Please be able to use email, write estimate letters to customers, and create some spreadsheets in excel.  

I would expect the shop to be able to perform regular maintenance of firearms but also be able to perform more exotic services, like scroll work, stippling, grip reductions, etc. You don’t have to be able to perform all of this work yourself, but I expect you to be able to lead those who can and identify a job well done, or a job that’s just crap.

We will be an equal opportunity shop, so be comfortable working with men, women, and everything in between, and working with people who like the same or opposite sex.

postcontent: This is a combo package for for solvent trap cleaning solutions for both 7.62 / .300 AND 5.56 / .223 cal guns. The 3 prong flash hider fits 5/8x24 threads, which is found on .308 / 7.62 AR10's and .300 Blackout AR15's. You permanently install the flash hider which has 3/4 NPT pipe thread on the outside. title: For Sale:  HK VP9 L.E 15RD MAGS X3: NIGHT SIGHTS!  NEW!
postcontent: In development for more than four years, the VP9 is Heckler & Koch’s latest handgun and the first striker fired HK since the renowned P7 series pistols were introduced in the 1980s.Experience gained by HK engineers with the recent P30 pistol had a direct influence on the design of the VP9, but the VP9 breaks new ground with its integration of a unique striker firing system with an enhanced HK “light pull” trigger. The net result is trigger quality unequaled in any production striker fired handgun.HK pioneered the first striker fired handguns, producing both the VP70 and P7 series, designs that impacted several models by HK competitors. But a superior trigger has eluded most striker fired pistol designs. The VP9 trigger surpasses those found on competitors. It has a short, light take-up with a solid, single action type break followed by a short positive reset.The VP9 trigger has a consistent pre-travel pull with a positive wall/crisp break. Typically, striker fired guns have a pre-travel pull that increases in weight as you go through the trigger stroke. With the VP9, you have a less than noticeable pre-travel pull until the trigger reaches the engagement point of the fire control parts prior to trigger break.The VP9 uses HK’s ergonomic handgun grip design that includes three changeable backstraps and six side panels— accommodating all hand sizes. Molded finger grooves in the front of the pistol’s grip also instinctively position an operator’s hand for optimal shooting. Only HK handguns have such a customized grip.Although influenced by other HK models, the VP9 has all the hallmarks of the latest, state-of-the-art handgun. All controls are completely ambidextrous. Slide releases are present on both sides of the frame and the magazine release can be easily activated by left- or right-handed shooters.A new feature is HK’s patented charging supports — simple components that are mounted on each side of the rear of the slide and provide better gripping leverage for racking the slide rearward. The charging supports speed reloading and make operating the VP9 easier for shooters with reduced hand strength. The VP pistols uses the proven P30 steel magazine; 15 and 10-round capacity available.The VP9 has an extended Picatinny MIL-STD-1913 rail molded into its polymer frame for mounting lights and accessories. The rail has been tested and certified to handle mounted accessories up to 5.6 ounces.The VP9’s proprietary captive flat recoil spring helps reduce the recoil forces effecting the operator and the handgun, improving shooter control during rapid firing and prolonging component service life.HK’s famous cold hammer forged barrel — made from cannon grade steel — ensures long service life. Similar HK barrels on 9 mm P30 models have fired more than 90,000 rounds in endurance tests in 2010. The polygonal bore profile, with no traditional lands-and-grooves rifling, contributes to longer service life as well as a slight increase in muzzle velocity.The VP9’s machined steel slide is protected from corrosion and wear by HK’s hostile environment finish and all metal components, including springs and pins have superior metallurgy.VP pistols are made in Heckler & Koch’s Oberndorf factory in southwest Germany. The VP9 is well-suited for civilian sport shooting, security, military, and law enforcement use.Covered by Heckler & Koch’s limited lifetime warranty, the HK VP9 is a solid design engineered with the famous long-term durability that make HK products especially cost-effective when subjected to total life cycle cost analysis. Suggested retail price of the VP9 is $719 with projected availability of July 2014.

title: For Sale:  ORIGINAL German-made 1921-1924 Deutsche Werke Ortgeis 32 Auto/ 7.65mm
postcontent:
PRICE Negotiable

Here is a piece of firearms history.  It is an German-made 1921-1924 Deutsche Werke Ortgeis 32 Auto / 7.65mm. This model was a common WWII era Finnish prison guard pistol, used in target competitions for it's accuracy, and known to be carried by outlaw John Dillenger.   For being over 90 years old, this gun is in GREAT working and consmetic condition.  I've fired over 150 rounds without any failures to feed, jams, or any issues whatsoever! I've disassembled and cleaned it thoroughly.  It's a rock solid piece and absolutely a BLAST to shoot. I can explain how to disassemble and clean and provide PDF manual and there are Youtube links to dis-assembly and cleaning.  It's not hard, but not quite as easy as modern pistols to take down.  It comes with an original magazine and an Uncle Mikes holster. I'll add 200 rounds of 32 Auto for a great day or two of fun at the range.  I can tell you the previous owner carried it as a personal backup throughout his enlisted time in Vietnam, so this gun has seen combat.
